.TH "fsverity_prepare_setattr" 9 "fsverity_prepare_setattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_prepare_setattr \- prepare to change a verity inode's attributes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsverity_prepare_setattr
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "struct iattr *attr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
dentry through which the inode is being changed
.IP "attr" 12
attributes to change
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Verity files are immutable, so deny truncates.  This isn't covered by the
open-time check because \fBsys_truncate\fP takes a path, not a file descriptor.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
